      • expression

        public static Expression expression(String expression,
                                    CompilationContext context)
        Compiles an expression.
        Parameters:
        expression - a String representing the expression to compile
        context - the compilation context to use. Can be used when it is necessary to pass in a non-standard field repository or functions library. The same context object may be reused across multiple compilations.
        Returns:
        an Expression object representing the result of the compilation process
        Throws:
        InvalidExpressionException - indicates that an error has occurred during the compilation

      • stringExpression

        public static StringExpression stringExpression(String expression,
                                                boolean disableLogging)
        This method behaves in a similar way to stringExpression(String) with the additional option to instruct the expressions compiler to refrain from logging when compiling the expression. This allows the evaluation of expressions in contexts where the logging subsystem is not yet available.
        Parameters:
        expression - an expression to compile
        disableLogging - If true, instructs the expressions compiler to refrain from logging when compiling the expression.
        Returns:
        a StringExpression
        Throws:
        ExpressionCompilationException - if a compilation issue occurs
        InvalidExpressionDataTypeException - if the resulting compiled expression is not of data type ExpressionDataType.STRING
